## Overview
<!-- The Assumption Register is a transversal artefact maintained across all phases. This document captures Phase 2 additions and updates the status of assumptions carried over from Phase 1. -->
This register records all assumptions made during Phase 2 — Requirements and Baseline. Assumptions are conditions believed to be true but not yet validated. Each assumption represents a risk: if invalidated, the project scope, schedule, or budget may be affected.

**Individual Assumption Entries:** See [assumption-register-entry.md.template](../assumption-register-entry.md.template) for the standard entry format used when logging new assumptions mid-phase.

**What is new in Phase 2:** Requirements elicitation typically surfaces assumptions about stakeholder availability, data quality, system integration behaviour, and regulatory interpretations. All such assumptions must be logged and assigned a validation date within this phase.

{{assumption_register_overview_notes}}

